.png","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":6,"Type":"title","Text":"Why Your Al Agent Keeps Forgetting Everything","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":247,"Y":685},"LeftTop":{"X":247,"Y":653},"RightBottom":{"X":935,"Y":685},"RightTop":{"X":935,"Y":653}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":7,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"Here is what used to happen inside my Al pipeline. I would build a client-facing agent, hand it a 2,000-word context dump at the top of every conversation, and watch it forget all of it the moment the session ended. Next call: start over. Same questions. Same setup. Same waste of time.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":247,"Y":789},"LeftTop":{"X":247,"Y":705},"RightBottom":{"X":1128,"Y":789},"RightTop":{"X":1128,"Y":705}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":8,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"I was running 6 Al sub-agents across my content operation and spending 80% of each session just re-orienting the agent on who the client was, what we had already covered, and what decisions had already been made.That is not automation. That is a very expensive to-do list.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":247,"Y":893},"LeftTop":{"X":247,"Y":811},"RightBottom":{"X":1133,"Y":893},"RightTop":{"X":1133,"Y":811}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":9,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"The fix was not a better prompt. It was memory architecture. Once I wired in the right memory types for each job,my agents started picking up exactly where they left off. Client context carried over. Decisions stuck.The same$5/day Al stack started doing work that used to take me 67 hours a week.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":247,"Y":997},"LeftTop":{"X":247,"Y":913},"RightBottom":{"X":1116,"Y":997},"RightTop":{"X":1116,"Y":913}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Inde